er chemistry yields serine, which then condenses with hydrothermal indole to give tryptophan.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_002", "rxn_006", "rxn_007", "rxn_009", "rxn_010"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_004", "mol_009", "mol_010", "mol_013"]}, {"pathway_id": "P3", "name": "Pyrrole-assisted hydrothermal indole route", "description": "Acetylene and ammonia form pyrrole in hydrothermal sulfide systems; pyrrole feeds the unresolved annulation step to indole in Fe-rich saponite nanoreactors, then indole couples with serine.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_008", "rxn_009", "rxn_010"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_012", "mol_013", "mol_010"]}, {"pathway_id": "P4", "name": "Hydrothermal pyruvate-alanine branch feeding direct tryptophan formation", "description": "Hydrothermal carbon fixation generates pyruvate and alanine as amino-donor/backbone components while indole forms in parallel; alanine-rich pools are taken as support for side-chain installation in Fe-saponite settings ending in tryptophan.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_002", "rxn_003", "rxn_004", "rxn_009", "rxn_010"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_005", "mol_006", "mol_013"]}, {"pathway_id": "P5", "name": "Surface HCN-serine route with hydrothermal indole input", "description": "Surface photochemistry generates HCN; hydrothermal carbon feeds formose sugar chemistry to glyceraldehyde; Strecker serine then reacts with hydrothermal indole to furnish tryptophan.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_005", "rxn_006", "rxn_007", "rxn_009", "rxn_010"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_007", "mol_009", "mol_010", "mol_013"]}, {"pathway_id": "P6", "name": "Strecker route from indole-3-acetaldehyde aminonitrile", "description": "A literature-theoretical pathway in which indole-3-acetaldehyde undergoes Strecker chemistry to a tryptophan aminonitrile, followed by hydrolysis to tryptophan.", "reaction_sequence": ["rxn_011", "rxn_012"], "key_intermediates": ["mol_014", "mol_015"]}, {"pathway_id": "P7", "name": "Hydrothermal indole plus surface HCN-assi